    "attributes": {
        "action": "Pressure the Indonesian government to put a stop to deforestation",
        "additional_details": "Nearly 60,000 hectares of forests have been cleared - an area the size of Chicago.\r\n \r\nA 2018 report by the Forest Stewardship Council (FSC) said there was no evidence that illegal fires had been set by palm oil companies. However the BBC obtained a copy which found \u201cevidence beyond reasonable doubt\u201d that 30,000 hectares of forest had been destroyed in breach of FSC regulations.",
        "background": "The British Government needs to pressure the Indonesian government to put a stop to deforestation by palm oil companies. The tribes who live in the rainforest in Papau New Guinea deserve justice. An area the size of Chicago has been destroyed.",
